snippet.textDisplay: It's a teaser, not a trailer. I don't want to see everything in the trailers. They are for sure going to show them in the next trailer. This is laying the groundwork, and I'm glad they didn't give it all away. They showed the suits, that was enough for now, letting us know that the original team was not forgotten and they are going to come back, and not as a cheap cameo like the 2016 film. Yes, it does have a Stranger Things vibe, but then again, Ghostbusters II was set up with that creepy undertone to it as well, and then brought the comedy back. I would imagine that will happen in this one as well. It's just a teaser to get us excited, the full trailer will show more.
